{{Underlinked|date=October 2017}} {{italics title}} '''''Budapester Zeitung''''' ('''''BZT''''') is a privately owned German-language weekly newspaper published in [[Budapest]], Hungary. It was established in April 1999 and has a circulation of about 7000 copies. Since 2003 there has been an English-language sister newspaper, ''[[The Budapest Times]]''. It is published by BZT Media Kft, founded by Berlin-born Jan Mainka. <ref name=bzt>{{cite web|url=http://www.budapester.hu/uber-uns/|title=Über uns|publisher=''Budapester Zeitung|accessdate=21 September 2015 |language=German}}</ref>
Since early 2014, BZT has been published in magazine format. Aimed primarily at German-language businessmen and diplomats living in Hungary, it covers politics, the economy, culture and local events as well as world news.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hro.ceu.edu/newspapers-and-magazines|title=Foreign Language Newspapers and Magazines |publisher=Central European University|accessdate=21 September 2015 |language=}}</ref><ref name=bzt/>
