[[File:Elevador da Ribeira (3577555121).jpg|thumb|The ''Elevador da Ribeira'']]
The '''''Elevador da Ribeira''''' or '''''Elevador da Lada''''' is a public elevator in [[Porto]], [[Portugal]]. It connects the neighbourhood of {{ill|Ribeira (Porto)|pt|lt=Ribeira}} (at no. 66 of Largo dos Arcos da Ribeira, near the [[Dom Luís I Bridge]])<ref name="visitporto"/> to the middle of the slope of Barredo, by means of a vertical lift and a footbridge.<ref name="elevare">{{cite web |last1=Vasconcelos |first1=António |title=Ascensor da Ribeira do Porto |url=http://www.elevare.pt/PDF/ele6/ah6.pdf |website=elevare |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20180509080728/http://www.elevare.pt/PDF/ele6/ah6.pdf |archivedate=9 May 2018 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>
It was designed by the architect António Moura, and its inauguration on 13 April 1994 was attended by President [[Mário Soares]] and other dignitaries.<ref name="elevare"/>
The lift is open from Monday to Friday from 08:00 to 20:00.<ref name="visitporto">{{cite web |title=View point – Lada Elevator (Ribeira) |url=http://www.visitporto.travel/visitar/paginas/viagem/DetalhesPOI.aspx?POI=1731 |website=Visit Porto |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20180629200927/http://www.visitporto.travel/visitar/paginas/viagem/DetalhesPOI.aspx?POI=1731 |archivedate=29 June 2018}}</ref>
