[[File:Flag Drenthe.svg|thumb|200px|The flag of Drenthe]]

The '''[[flag]] of [[Drenthe]]''' was adopted on February 19, 1947. 

The colours of the flag (red and white) are the traditional [[Saxony|Saxon]] colours and also those of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Utrecht|Archbishop of Utrecht]] by whom Drenthe was governed in the past.

The six stars represent the six ancient regions (dingspil) and the castle is a reference to the city [[Coevorden]] from where the province has been governed for a long time.

