{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}} {{Infobox film | name = Ghadi | image = Ghadi (film).jpg | caption = Film poster | director = [[Amin Dora]] | producer = Gabriel Chamoun | writer = [[Georges Khabbaz]] | starring = Georges Khabbaz | music = | cinematography = Karim Ghorayeb | editing = | distributor = | released = {{Film date|2013|10|31|df=yes}} | runtime = 95 minutes | country = Lebanon | language = Arabic | budget = }}
'''''Ghadi''''' ({{lang-ar|غدي}}) is a 2013 Lebanese [[drama film]] directed by [[Amin Dora]]. The film was originally selected as the Lebanese entry for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[86th Academy Awards]]<ref name="Rope">{{cite web|url=http://www.ropeofsilicon.com/oscar-contenders/foreign-language/ |title=Foreign Language Oscar Contenders |accessdate=27 September 2013 |work=Rope of Silicon |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002044950/http://www.ropeofsilicon.com/oscar-contenders/foreign-language/ |archivedate=2 October 2013 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref name="Lebanon">{{cite web |url=http://www.radiosawa.com/content/lebanon-nominates-ghadi-for-oscar-foreign-film/233125.html |title= لبنان يرشح فيلم 'غدي' للأوسكار |accessdate=25 September 2013|work=Radio Sawa}}</ref> in a two-way race over Lara Saba's ''[[Blind Intersections]]''.<ref name= "Lebanon" /> When the film's release date was moved from 26 September 2013 to 31 October 2013,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemacity.com.lb/Movies/Details/180/Ghadi?noGallery=1 |title=Lebanon |accessdate=8 October 2013 |work=CinemaCity.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131112092405/http://www.cinemacity.com.lb/Movies/Details/180/Ghadi?noGallery=1 |archivedate=12 November 2013 |df=dmy }}</ref> it no longer met the eligibility dates and ''Blind Intersections'' became the [[List of Lebanese submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|official submission from Lebanon]]. The film was submitted the following year as Lebanon's official submission, but was not nominated.<ref name="Lebanon-Gov">{{cite web |url=http://www.nna-leb.gov.lb/fr/show-news/34056/Araiji-nomme-Ghadi-pour-repr%C3%A9senter-le-Liban-aux-Oscars-2014 |title=Araiji nomme "Ghadi" pour représenter le Liban aux Oscars 2014 |accessdate=30 September 2014 |work=Lebanese Ministry of Information}}</ref>
==Cast== * [[Georges Khabbaz]] as Leba Saba * [[Lara Matar]] as Lara, Leba's Wife * [[Christine Choueiri]] as Sophie
