{{Infobox military unit | unit_name = Seychelles People's Defence Force Air Wing | image = Flag of Seychelles.svg | image_size = | caption = | dates = 1978–present | country = {{flag|Seychelles}} | allegiance = | branch = [[Air force]] | type = | role = | size = 4 fixed-wing aircraft | command_structure = [[Seychelles People's Defence Force]] | garrison = [[Seychelles International Airport]] | garrison_label = Headquarters | nickname = SPDFAF | patron = | motto = | colors = | colors_label = Red and Green | march = | mascot = | equipment = | equipment_label = | battles = [[1981 Seychelles coup d'état attempt]] | anniversaries = | decorations = | battle_honours = <!-- Commanders --> | notable_commanders = <!-- Insignia --> | identification_symbol = [[File:Roundel of Seychelles.svg|80px]] | identification_symbol_label = Roundel | identification_symbol_2 = [[File:Seychelles Coast Guard Aviation Insigna.svg|80px]] | identification_symbol_2_label = Former Roundel | aircraft_attack = | aircraft_bomber = | aircraft_electronic = | aircraft_fighter = | aircraft_interceptor = | aircraft_patrol = | aircraft_recon = | aircraft_trainer = | aircraft_transport = | current_commander = [[President Danny Faure]] | current_commander_label = | ceremonial_chief = | ceremonial_chief_label = | start_date = 24 June 1978 }} [[File:Beech 1900D, Islands Development Company JP9934.jpg|thumb|A Islands Development Company Beech 1900]] The '''Seychelles People's Defence Force Air Wing''' is the air force of the Seychelles People's Defence Force.
== History == The Seychelles People's Defence Force Air Wing was formed in 1978 with help from India with a Cessna A-150 Aerobat trainer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/indian-ocean/se-spdf.htm|title=Seychelles People�s Defense Forces (SPDF)|last=Pike|first=John|website=www.globalsecurity.org|access-date=2018-07-09}}</ref> in 1997 the SAF split from the coast guard. The Island Development Corporation (IDC) has an assortment of aircraft. The aircraft inventory of the Island Development Corporation includes: One Cessna 150, one Beech 1900.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://smallairforces.blogspot.com/2011/02/welcome-to-seychelles.html|title=Small Air Forces: Welcome to the Seychelles!|last=Rat|first=King|date=2011-02-18|website=Small Air Forces|access-date=2018-07-10}}</ref>
The Island Development Corporation is a small component of the SDFAF for SAR and patrols. The aircraft bare civil markings and registration.
== Inventory == The Seychelles Air Force was originally formed in 1978 as the Air Wing and has the following aircraft:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=29310:india-donates-do-228-surveillance-aircraft-to-seychelles&catid=35:Aerospace&Itemid=107|title=India donates Do 228 surveillance aircraft to Seychelles - defenceWeb|last=Martin|first=Guy|website=www.defenceweb.co.za}}</ref>
