{{speciesbox | name = ''Tarentola nicolauensis'' | image = | image_caption = | status = LC | status_system = IUCN3.1 | status_ref = | genus = Tarentola | species = substituta | authority = [[Hans Hermann Schleich|Schleich]] (1984) | synonyms = | synonyms_ref =<ref name="RDB"/> }} '''''Tarentola nicolauensis''''' (English name: '''São Nicolau wall gecko''') is a [[species]] of [[gecko]]s in the [[Family (biology)|family]] [[Phyllodactylidae]]. The species is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[Cape Verde]] Islands.<ref name="RDB">{{NRDB species|genus=Tarentola |species=nicolauensis|accessdate=23 March 2017}}</ref> The species was named in by [[Hans Hermann Schleich]] in 1984.
The species are found in the islands of São Vicente and São Nicolau, it may once be found in the island of [[Santa Luzia, Cape Verde|Santa Luzia]].<ref name="RDB"/>
==Taxonomy== The subspecies were elevated from ''Tarentola caboverdiana nicolauensis'' by Vasconcelos, Perera, Geniez, Harris & Carranza en 2012.<ref>Vasconcelos, Perera, Geniez, Harris & Carranza, ''An integrative taxonomic revision of the Tarentola geckos (Squamata, Phyllodactylidae) of the Cape Verde Islands.'' Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 2012, vol. 164, no. 2, p. 328-360</ref>
