'''TIML Radio Limited''', was a wholly owned subsidiary of [[The Times Group]], (who are the publishers of [[The Times of India]] and [[The Economic Times]]) were the owners of British radio stations [[Absolute Radio]], [[Absolute 80s]], [[Absolute 90s]] and [[Absolute Classic Rock]] prior to the groups sale to [[Bauer Media]] in 2013.<ref>[http://www.londonstockexchange.com/LSECWS/IFSPages/MarketNewsPopup.aspx?id=1856978&source=RNS Sale of Virgin Radio to TIML for £53.2 million]{{Dead link|date=June 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }} London Stock Exchange</ref><ref>[http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/News/News_By_Company/Corporate_Trends/Times_Group_buys_UKs_Virgin_Radio_for_Rs_448_cr/articleshow/3089589.cms Times Group buys UK's Virgin Radio for Rs 448 cr] The Economic Times</ref><ref>[http://www.campaignindia.in/news/times_of_india_company_buys_virgin_radio_holdings_ltd Times of India company buys Virgin Radio Holdings Ltd] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080607030840/http://www.campaignindia.in/news/times_of_india_company_buys_virgin_radio_holdings_ltd |date=7 June 2008 }} Campaign India</ref><ref>[http://www.absoluteradio.co.uk/about/legal/corporate_and_trademark_information.html Corporate and trademark information] Absolute Radio</ref>

