{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
{{Politics of Benin}}
The '''Union for Future Benin''' ({{Lang-fr|Union pour le Bénin du futur}}) is an electoral alliance in [[Benin]]. In the [[legislative]] [[elections in Benin|elections]] held on 30 March 2003, the party was member of the Presidential Movement, the alliance of supporters of [[Mathieu Kérékou]], who had won the 2001 presidential elections, and won 31 out of 83 seats. The most important of the member parties are the [[Action Front for Renewal and Development]] (''Front d'action pour le rénouveau et le développement'') and the [[Social Democratic Party (Benin)|Social Democratic Party]] (''Parti Social-Démocrate'').

